- **(b)**: A Bode plot of the differential-mode gain (|A_dm|) in dB versus frequency \( f \) on a logarithmic scale. The gain is constant at low frequencies and decreases at -6 dB/octave from \( \frac{1}{2\pi RC_t} \).
- **(c)**: A Bode plot of the Common-Mode Rejection Ratio (CMRR) in dB versus frequency \( f \) on a logarithmic scale. The CMRR decreases at -6 dB/octave initially and then at -12 dB/octave from \( \frac{1}{2\pi RC_t} \).

